description: These meaty and gluten free spring rolls are simple and filling.
name: Gluten Free Spring Rolls with Diced Beef Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 medium white onion, peeled and diced
8 sheets rice paper, thawed if frozen

recipeInstructions.text: Heat up a non-stick pan to a medium heat with 1 tablespoon of sesame oil.
Fry the beef for 6 minutes while tossing or until it starts to brown on each side, remove to cutting board, allow to cool then dice.
Using the same pan, add the onion, garlic and chilli and cook for another 3 minutes until the mixture is dry or drain the excess fats.
Dip the rice paper into warm water for 5 seconds.
Add diced beef back into pan and mix, remove ingredients the heat and place a large spoonful into the centre of a sheet of pastry, fold over the edges and roll tightly.
Serve with a choice of dips/condiments.
